# Scope Control (MANDATORY)

## This Is a 7-Day Sprint

Every decision must pass the filter: "Does this help ship the demo by Sunday?"

## In Scope (build these)

- Single lesson: fraction equivalence (3.NF.A.3a/b, 4.NF.A.1)
- Deterministic Fraction Engine with property-based tests
- Scripted dialogue system (ScriptedTutorBrain) with JSON scripts
- Visual fraction manipulative (split, combine, compare)
- 4 guided practice problems + 3 assessment problems
- Chat panel with Sam persona
- Progress dots, completion screen, sound effects
- sessionStorage checkpointing + recovery
- iPad Safari support, PWA offline
- Vercel deployment

## Out of Scope (do NOT build these)

- LLM-powered conversational agent (build the TutorBrain interface seam, not the implementation)
- Multiple lessons or a lesson library
- Student accounts, login, or cross-session persistence
- Teacher dashboard or classroom management
- RAG-based pedagogical engine
- "Smashing" interaction (fraction addition) — acknowledge gracefully in the reducer, do not implement
- Full accessibility audit beyond Tier 1 ARIA + keyboard fallback
- Server-side anything — no backend, no database, no API

## When Tempted to Add Scope

- Do NOT add features not listed above
- Do NOT refactor code that works "to make it cleaner" during the sprint
- Do NOT build infrastructure for future lessons
- Do NOT integrate an LLM — the scripted brain is the prototype deliverable
- If you find a future improvement, note it in a comment or the README — do not build it
